The current way to set an editor to read only mode is:

``` js
var editor = atom.views.getView(editor);
// set it to read only mode.
editorView.removeAttribute('tabindex');
// remove the cursor line decoration.
editor.getDecorations({class: 'cursor-line', type: 'line'})[0].destroy();
```

There should be a better way to do that.

